- I brought you back your flashlight.
- What?

459
00:34:59,629 --> 00:35:02,427
- Your face is wet.
- Oh, go away and let me alone.

460
00:35:02,589 --> 00:35:07,140
I was only trying to...
I brought back...

461
00:35:09,149 --> 00:35:11,140
Ow!

462
00:35:15,709 --> 00:35:19,145
Hey! I borrowed your flashlight again.

463
00:35:20,989 --> 00:35:24,140
- What happened?
- I sat on this. It was in my bed.

464
00:35:26,029 --> 00:35:29,863
- "You left town so quickly..."
- Go away, will you? Go on.

465
00:35:32,029 --> 00:35:34,099
Hey, Swiv. Swiv, where are you?

466
00:35:34,309 --> 00:35:36,459
- I don't know. I'm in the dark.
- Quiet!

467
00:35:36,629 --> 00:35:38,699
Come here.
Let's have that light, will you?

468
00:35:40,149 --> 00:35:42,868
"I didn't get to give
this back to you.

469
00:35:43,029 --> 00:35:46,339
Inasmuch as I refused it when
Mr. Cortland tried to give it to me...

470
00:35:46,509 --> 00:35:49,421
...I see no reason
why I should take it from you.

471
00:35:49,589 --> 00:35:50,738
Sheila Winthrop.

472
00:35:50,909 --> 00:35:53,981
P.S. May I compliment
you again on your..."

473
00:35:54,149 --> 00:35:58,586
- Chivalry.
- "Chivalry." Who's Sheila Winthrop?

474
00:35:59,029 --> 00:36:03,784
I didn't realize it before,
but she is a very sweet young lady.

475
00:36:10,469 --> 00:36:14,348
That's the first time I ever heard
of a rabbit giving a carrot back.

476
00:36:18,869 --> 00:36:21,827
I just want to tell you I won't
need your flashlight anymore.

477
00:36:21,989 --> 00:36:24,059
Look here, Swivel Tongue.
If you come near me...

478
00:36:24,229 --> 00:36:26,584
- Quiet!
- You guys be quiet.

479
00:36:26,749 --> 00:36:30,025
It's him. He's making all the noise.
You'll wake everybody up.

480
00:36:30,189 --> 00:36:32,145
One, two, ten.

481
00:36:32,829 --> 00:36:37,425
- I'm a heel. That's what I am, a heel.
- Shut up, you heel!

482
00:37:27,029 --> 00:37:29,304
Ouch! Ouch!

483
00:37:29,589 --> 00:37:31,898
Ouch, ouch! Ouch!

484
00:37:32,109 --> 00:37:35,419
- Ouch! Ouch!
- What's going on here?

485
00:37:37,189 --> 00:37:39,942
- Come on. Get up. Wake up.
- Stop him.

486
00:37:40,109 --> 00:37:44,148
Get up. Wake up.
Come on, come out of it.

487
00:37:44,309 --> 00:37:46,903
So you'll hit me too, will you?

488
00:38:02,309 --> 00:38:05,460
Two days in the guardhouse.
If you ask me, you got off easy.

489
00:38:05,629 --> 00:38:08,780
- But I tell you, I wasn't drinking.
- You gave a good imitation of it.

490
00:38:08,949 --> 00:38:11,383
I was just having a bad dream.

491
00:38:19,149 --> 00:38:23,700
He kept jabbing at me with that
pitchfork. The last thing I remember...

492
00:38:28,269 --> 00:38:30,829
- There he is again!
- Hey you!

493
00:38:31,029 --> 00:38:33,224
Say. Wait a minute.

494
00:38:38,389 --> 00:38:41,108
- That's for the pitchfork.
- You'll get 10 years for this.

495
00:38:41,309 --> 00:38:45,860
I just wanted to tell you that I'm
really not Miss Winthrop's brother.

496
00:38:46,029 --> 00:38:49,021
- What happened in New York was a gag.
- That gun was no gag.

497
00:38:49,189 --> 00:38:52,181
- It wasn't loaded.
- I don't like your sense of humour.

498
00:38:52,349 --> 00:38:55,307
You better keep away because
every time I see you, I'll bop you.

499
00:38:55,509 --> 00:38:58,819
- Do you know who that man is?
- No, and what's more, I don't care.

500
00:38:58,989 --> 00:39:02,459
Okay, buddy, I'm gonna
let you find out all by yourself.

501
00:39:24,629 --> 00:39:27,223
- Mrs. Barton?
- Yes. I'm looking for my son.

502
00:39:27,389 --> 00:39:29,698
- I'll tell Captain Barton you're here.
- Thank you.

503
00:39:29,869 --> 00:39:31,302
Tom will be so glad to see you.

504
00:39:31,469 --> 00:39:35,018
I hope. He spent his leave convincing
us to come here instead of Florida.

505
00:39:35,189 --> 00:39:38,545
Don't let her fool you. She could
hardly wait to get out of New York.

506
00:39:42,629 --> 00:39:46,622
Captain Barton sends his regrets.
He'll be delayed a few minutes.

507
00:39:46,789 --> 00:39:49,542
- Where's the music coming from?
- From the guardhouse, ma'am.

508
00:39:49,709 --> 00:39:51,540
- Thank you.
- Yes, ma'am.

